< Review>
This map and map buying experience exceeded all my expectations.  His quality is outstanding.  Thick laminate.  Colors perfect.  Size is great.  I expected some foul up in shipping such a large map (48x60) but it came in a FedEx triangular tube and it was like I bought it in the store.  Best of all, it was cheaper than any other map I saw.  I HIGHLY recommend MapSales to anyone wanting a high quality map.</Review>

This place is AWESOME! I've been to a lot of coffee houses in LA and the West Coast. I'm from Seattle so I know what I'm talking about. This is one of the best coffee houses I've been to in LA. 0x80dd3630f594b485:0xcd814e39d3e0c24d<//gmapID>
<Text>If you're staying in a neighborhood, and just finding a hotel room -- any hotel room -- is all that brought you there, you feel as if you won the lottery when you find a place like Sirens. As others have said, it's roomy, eclectic (local artists on the walls), chill, and welcoming. Very tasty cup of Costa Rican coffee, and the ham/egg/cheese croissant was better than any I have had -- a little toasty, enough to warm the fillings and melt the cheese, but not enough to dry out the croissant. The WiFi password is posted obviously -- that makes me feel as if it's OK to stay a while. I don't intent to park here, but it's the kind of place where the next great American novel could well be written. (And not by me -- ha!)
Very comfortable here, and will come again if my travels take me to San Pedro.< /Text><user_name>Peter Sterpe</user_name><pics>None<//pics><rating>5</rating></record></dataset><record>

< Review>
This is indeed a beautiful place, with ambient atmosphere and decor. For a coffee house it is definitely high scale especially for the area of San Pedro that its in. And I hate to give a bad review, but I'll be honest. I do have to say that it's way too pricey for the quality of food you are getting. The coffee is  good, but easily Peets coffee is as good or better, without the hassle from staff on the peticulars of your drink order. The staff try to enforce too many rules, while being too inexperienced. Just because it's a smaller coffee shop doesn't mean they shouldn't keep up with the customs of most places. In fact that's why they should do like their competitors and not overcharge, if they want to stay open. They have too many rules to fit the cozy atmosphere of the place. When you go there, go to enjoy the dining of the shop itself, but dont be suprised if the service is less than desirable.</Review>

< Text>
Great quiet clean place, great customer service, and great snacks and coffee. They have quite a few vegan options which is something I really appreciate. The only thing that ruins the experience is their wifi. It's difficult to connect to the wifi and once you get it to connect I believe you get two hours free and then you have to either pay through TWC or get a 30 minute trail. Sometimes when trying to connect it disconnects and when you go through the process to connect again it says you've already used your two hours. Please get this fixed. I'm a college student who lives near by and would love to spend my study time in the inspiring space you've created.<//Text>

<rate>4</rate>< Text>
Friendly staff. If you want to park close you're going to have to pay the meter during the day. Wi-Fi only gives you 2 hours and get out afterwards. A little hard to figure out there WiFi you'll have to ask the friendly lady behind the counter how it works. Tea selection was good although I think they gave me the wrong tea. I asked for a lemon ginger and I think I got a Rooibos. Not crazy about coffee so I don't know anything about it. they had tons of Nibley little Goods that were freshly baked and they were amazing. This place is as big as a barn so there's plenty of seating for all. It has nice little nooks to add to the coziness and like home feeling. Electricity is hard to find for your laptop. Elsewise this place was clean beautiful and I would go here again with Mom for Saturday coffee.🍪< /Text>

If you are a pop culture nerd like me, don't miss TFAW at Universal Studios CityWalk! They have comics, action figures, t-shirts, and all the yummy goodies from Dracula, Frankenstein's Creature and the rest of the Undead Universal Gang :L (yeah, I'm an undead freak). By all means, my fav store in Los Angeles.</Text>

<Pics>None</Pics><time>1527653849101<//time>< Text>
Nice indoor range. The staff is knowledgeable and friendly. Good selection of rentals. The range itself is in decent shape. Good ventilation. Ammo selection is decent as well. Lots of options for memberships. I will say that it would be nice if they were open later, as the people who get off work at 5pm may not get to shoot.  Good parking. Good selection of paper targets. Would be nice if you could shoot other things there, like I saw at another range- ( they had stuffed animals you could shoot or save if you wanted. That was kinda fun) If you go by yourself, bring your own firearm or else you will have to make an awkward call to someone who knows you, so they can tell the staff you won’t kill yourself or anyone else there. ( I understand in today’s climate why this is necessary, but it still is awkward) Still, this place is worth the trip if you come early enough<//Text>

<Text>We drove from Santa Barbara for Island View since there is no indoor ranges in Santa Barbara. We've gone to shooter's paradise before but due to their ammo restrictions I wanted to try Island View this time. I'm glad I did, everything from the look of the range to the people staffing it were better. The only restrictions on ammo was that it was brass, which is pretty usual. They also had a happy hour special where if you got a box of ammo, your lane fee was only 5 bucks which was nice. The range master Hugo was a great guy and was willing to give us tips when we asked. Their rental gun selection is pretty great as well. Overall it was a fun experience, we'll be back. Thanks guys.</Text>< Pictures>

< Review>
I rate Island View Enterprises 5+ stars!

The staff is courteous and pays attention to the customer. I took seven foreign language students to experience shooting in the U.S. and the staff, especially Adrian, was patient in answering questions and recommending handguns and long guns for the group to shoot.

I have shot at Island before but never with a large group. Every effort was made for the students to feel safe as the staff provide basic gun safety to the group before they started shooting.

My plans are to visit Island again.</Review>

<text>I seriously wanted to give this place a 5 star review. Most indoor ranges I've been to are staffed with arrogant military wannabe's that are rude and act they are in some position of authority because they are wearing a sidearm. I was so surprised with how courteous the young gentlemen was at the counter helping my girlfriend and I. It put a smile on my face and I even told her how rare this is. At least to me. The place was VERY clean and the prices were average and he gave me a military discount. Everything perfect until this...

My 1911 jammed twice on my girl towards the end of our shoot. The first time the range safety officer who was an older heavy set guy took the gun out of her hands before she had a chance to do anything unsafe. A little preemptive unless he's a psychic. The 2nd time which was on our very last round of ammunition she just set the gun down and walked away because she was scared the safety guy was going to rush her again. I approached, cleared the weapon, and reloaded the magazine. Set the gun down next to magazine and walked away so she could finish. Before she got to the gun the officer cut her off, grabbed my gun and said "you guys are out of here". I asked why and he would not give me a reason. It was all very inappropriate. If he can't control his urge to pick on pretty girls because he's insecure or something. He shouldn't be allowed to supervise when attractive women are shooting. He knew we had one round left and just had to kick us out. It was ridiculous and I felt embarrassed to say the least.

I was a United States Marine Corps Sergeant. I was also a M240 G machine gunner during Operation al-Fajr. I know weapons safety just as good as anyone. I sincerely believe this happened to us because she was pretty not because she was being unsafe.

Because of this experience I will not recommended this place to anyone.

Semper Fi<//text>< Date>

<Rating>3<//Rating><text>I would have given this place 5 stars however the range/store have taken a step back this past year. The range no longer allows CCW holders to draw from a holster. Given there aren't many outdoor opportunities here, many of us relied on IVE allowing CCW holders the ability to train from a holster. They also limited rapid fire for CCW holder. Thus a CCW holder can no longer perform drills that require rapid fire (e.g., 2/1, triple bills, etc). I understand the safety reasons behind not allowing newbs to do this, but a range member and CCW holder should be allowed to train in a realistic format. Next, the store has essentially closed and this is now only a range. You have to make appointments to buy guns, order guns, or PPT. This has really made me start using Shooter's Paradise more often again. Too bad because I truly like the staff here and the cleanliness. However, lack of store hours as well as more restrictive range rules for experienced CCW holders/members has made IVE drop down in my review.<//text>< pics>

<Rate>4< /Rate>< Review>
Spent several hours in their range on different occasions: well ventilated, clean, supervised, systematic, comfortable. Purchased from them: competitive prices, uncondescending staff, helpful with paperwork, poor [no] follow up on requested specialty items (eg: chokes, mags, holsters that are not offered on premises). Overall, a well run facility. If you are interested in an item the asking price will be fair, they'll be happy to show and explain key points of functionality, and will be a smooth transaction. Of all gun stores in Ventura County this is the only one i'll continue to purchase big ticket items from. Not to say the others aren't good stores (with the exception of Blueline Ammo - but thats a whole other review). Islandview just has what i'm looking for.<//Review>

<Review>I have now worked with Hans Art automotive twice now. Both times I have been shown through and through how trustworthy and excellent they are as a business. The first time Hans (the owner) literally diagnosed and fixed my problem over the phone without even seeing the vehicle (I did the work myself). The second I took it in and test-drove it with a mechanic and we were able to trouble-shoot the problem on the spot. Both times I was never charged a penny. I am an experienced mechanic so do most of the work on my own cars but living here I don't have access to a shop so am limited on what I can do.

I do need to have my clutch replaced which is something that I can't do with my current access to a shop, so I 100% will be bringing my car here to have that done in the next couple weeks. I have never worked with a mechanic shop where I felt this confident that I would have the work done at an extremely high quality rate and not end up being screwed over. They may not have the cheapest quotes, if you were to ask around you could probably find someone willing to do the work cheaper, but it's 100% better to have it done right the first time by people who won't screw you over or find issues that aren't actually issues (I've had other mechanics do that many times).
If Hans say something needs to be done, I would trust them, and that comes from a position that I RARELY ever trust mechanics since my dealings with them have always been so fraught with fear, uncertainty and doubt. (telling you you need work you don't, charging for things they don't even do, etc... look around at other mechanics and this is so commonly the norm)
10/10 would recommend. Unless you already have and trust a mechanic, don't trust anyone else and just take your car here. They will be fair and fix your issues.<//Review><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< user_name>

I don't know anything about cars, and I don't drive my car very often, but they know my car and they are always so helpful in answering all my questions. They always let me know what work really needs to be done on it and what doesn't, and even advised me to spread the repairs out over several months so that I don't dump too much money at once into such an old car in case something happens to it. Since I don't know anything about cars, they could easily take advantage of me and try to tell me that it's urgent to fix some of the things that are wrong with my car. <rate>1< /rate>< Review>
I tried to order a ring from brilliant earth for an engagement. I gave myself ample time (6 weeks) according to their website and I confirmed with a representative from the company the ring would be ready before placing the order. The ring was set to arrive 2 weeks before but the day before the shipping date, a month after I placed the order, the company finally contacted me to tell me they didn't have the diamond in their possession and didn't know when they would. They sent me some other options that they said they could have ready in time but I did not find them comparable to the diamond I had spent weeks and hours selecting. They offered to send out a "showroom" piece until they had possession of the diamond. When the showroom ring showed up only 3 days before the engagement it was undersized and not even the same ring design. I tried contacting the customer support member that had convinced me not to cancel the order and try to source the ring locally but instead go with the showroom ring but he has not responded to multiple emails or calls. needless to say they ruined the engagement I planned on a romantic getaway and still have my money tied up so I can't even purchase another ring. Use another company like James Allen or Blue Nile.<//Review>

<Rate>1<//Rate>< review>
After purchasing an engagement ring, I took the ring to a GIA gemologist for an insurance appraisal. The appraisal was alarmingly lower than the color and clarity rating which Brilliant Earth had provided and advertised. I considered the appraisal was possibly an outlier, so I took the ring to a second GIA certified gemologist for an insurance appraisal. I have now taken the ring to five independent GIA gemologists and found Brilliant Earth had misrepresented and inflated the gemological rating. On average, the color rating was at least one scale lower and the clarity was at least two scales lower than what was advertised and sold to me. I addressed the issue with Brilliant Earth and they informed me 30 days had passed and they could do nothing to help.

As a first time buyer, I feel my good faith has been completely violated and inexperienced buyers should be extremely cautious when buying from Brilliant Earth.< /review>

<text>My husband and I were in the area and shopping for jewelry. On my phone I was able to look up all the stores in La Jolla where we were staying and this came up with the rest. I was not familiar with the store and we stopped by. When we arrived the door indicated we had to ring a bell. No problem, we do that at many of the high end jewelry stores we visit for security reasons. Bell rung. No answer. Bell rung again. A zaftig, blonde opens the door and as we walk in says "and you are...?" as I am walking in to the room. There are only two small jewelry cases in the whole space and I am perplexed by this question and the room, so I reply "I am someone who likes jewelry?" hoping I have passed some kind of test that they do not give out at Graff, Winston or any other high end jewelers we have patronized. I wander to the two small cases and say are these the only items you have? It is a case of simple diamond engagement rings in the 1-2 carat range. That is all that is displayed and there are only a handful. She replies, no the showroom is actually behind that door and points to what must be the most special place in the whole gemological universe based on her demenor. But, she does not ask if we would like to see the room. At that point I say I am so sorry, is your store by appointment only? We clearly are interrupting what must be a very busy day of...secret things behind the special door?
And we would not know if it was by appointment only as we looked up stores on my iPhone maps app. At that point she says is there something you are looking for? In a fairly petulant voice. I indicated we were! And tried to tell her what it was we were shopping for.  From there it continued to go down hill while she was obnoxious and rude until my husband literally said, stop, we are leaving, this is silly.
Brilliant Earth. I do not know what you are trying to accomplish with your show rooms but if you want to create less of these messes and it were me, I would: 1-place signage on your doors that says by appointment only if that is the case. 2-train your employees how to communicate that in a professional manner to someone who is shopping for jewelry and mistakes your store for a place to spend large amounts of money. 3-perhaps also mention that when you have offended people to the point the husband is storming out with the wife that the sales snot should not yell after them in a taunting voice, "would you like my business card?!" Your store is full of cameras so you can enjoy this performance she put on yourself's if you doubt anything I am writing. While viewing please note the jewelry I am wearing. Normally, when sales personal in a jewelry store can see we buy that type of jewelry they take us fairly serioulsy. I have never been treated like that in a Target store much less a Harry Winston. So yes, Brilliant Earth is very high end, if you are looking to spend a few hundred thousand on a cocktail ring, as we were, they are not the store for you. Thank gosh our money spends in the rest of the stores in La Jolla! It was pretty comical though and a novel experience.</text>< Pics>

<Review>I absolutely love my ring and was devastated when I noticed that the band had cracked. I was so upset I was in tears. It appears the ring cracked around the solder joint. I'm an accountant, I sit at my desk for 50+ hours a week. I never wear my ring when I workout, and I always take it off when sleeping, showering, etc. There was zero stress put on the ring, and it should not have cracked, especially after 9 months after it was purchased.

I emailed Naomi Czerwinskyj, who my fiance purchased my ring from, letting her know the band of my ring had cracked. I asked her if I could come in to drop off the ring, and asked if the ring repair would be covered under warranty since the ring was purchased less than 9 months ago. She responds to my email, and proposes two different days for me to come in. But she never addressed whether or not the repair would be covered under warranty. I send a second email, and attached two pictures from my proposal, and again ask if the repair will be covered under warranty. She does not respond. 11 days later, I send another email asking if I can come in to drop off my ring. Again, she does not respond.

Since Naomi was not responding to me, I called the generic Brilliant Earth phone number and left a voicemail, and didn't receive a call back for 2 days. Someone named Isabel (person #2 that I was in contact with) called me back and left me a voicemail. Here's the problem, as soon as you try calling Brilliant Earth back, you just get a line that rings and rings and no one ever answers the phone! I gave up after 20 minutes of being on hold and hung up.

Then I received a response from the emails I sent Naomi from another representative, Tory Cabot (person #3 that I was in contact with). Tory tells me they're responding on behalf of Naomi, they'd be happy to get a repair appointment set up for me, and asks when would be a good time to give me a call. I respond to Tory's email within 3 minutes saying that I was free and asked them to call me. I get zero response from Tory. I call the phone number listed on Tory's email signature and leave a voicemail. I get zero call back.

The next morning, I received a call from Christoper another representative (person #4 I'm in contact with) on behalf of Tory. Again, I was at work when I received the call and I missed it. So when I tried calling back, the same exact thing happened - the phone just kept ringing and no one ever answered. I again gave up after being on hold for more than 10 minutes.

I was so frustrated that I finally gave up and just made an appointment online. Apparently, this is what I should have done in the first place. I assumed that the person my fiance purchased a very expensive ring from would have been more responsive and helpful (especially when she knows we haven't even purchased a matching wedding band yet).

I go into the showroom to drop off my ring for repair. Athina (person #5) was very nice during my appointment. I dropped off the ring last Sunday, July 22nd. She informed me that the ring would be shipped out to San Francisco and that we should expect to receive an update by Friday, July 27th at the latest. She told to me call Sarah (person #6) if we didn't hear an update by Friday.

On Monday, July 30th my fiance called the phone number on Sarah's card and waited on hold for 90 minutes before finally hanging up. He then went on Brilliant Earth's website and used the online chat feature. Isabel tells him that the ring is at the San Francisco location and we should be hearing from the repair team by tomorrow.

It is now Tuesday, July 31st and we have heard zero communication from a Brilliant Earth representative. They have had my ring in their custody for 10 days and we have received zero updates on the status of what repairs are needed. We also still have no idea if the repair is covered under warranty.

This is by far the worst customer service experience I have ever had. It's repulsive to think that a company would treat you so poorly after spending so much money with them.< /Review><pics>None</pics><resp>None</resp>< GmapID>

< review>
Hidden little gem of a park. Basketball courts, walking trail, indoor hall, playground area, exercise equipment, ample parking, large open field. Pets are brought in although they are not allowed. Can get crowded at times. Closes early due to surrounding areas I suppose. Clean and plenty of flowers and trees.<//review>

< Time>
1527643259257<//Time>
<rate>5< /rate><Text>Dover Saddlery has been amazing all the years I have been riding horses. It only gets better every time I go. Prices can be quite high, but the tack is made with very soft, smooth leather. I personally would recommend shopping at Dover during sales, especially the huge sale around September. During the sales, prices drop A LOT, and all the tack is in great condition. For example: In the sale in Fall I got a Dressage bridle that was in perfect shape for 30 dollars and a super soft lunge line for 10 dollars. Keep in mind  the sale in Fall is selling mostly used and returned items that did not work for people and their horses, which is I think why the prices are so low. So far though the tack and items from the Fall sale were perfect and still are in great shape! Over all Dover Saddlery is a great place for riders to buy tack and other items that will last for a long time!!! Thank you Dover.< /Text>< Pics>

< Review>
I was very disappointed in my visit to the Moraga Dover store today. I went in to exchange some Back on Track polo wraps and purchase new boots and a bit and dealt with a woman named Karen. Dover used to have a 100% satisfaction guarantee, you could return anything at any point. I talked to an employee this past Christmas about returning the polos and she said it wouldn’t be a problem despite the fact that I had bought them a year ago. I took them in to exchange and was told very rudely that because I had purchased them over a year ago I would not be able to exchange them. To be clear they were not worn out they had only been used three times and I was not pleased with the fit. When I brought up the fact that you used to be able to return thing much past a year she told me I was wrong and that they were a company not a “Library” I drove over an hour and a half to go to the actual Dover store and do a return. I work in retail myself and I don’t have a problem with the fact that their exchange/return policy has changed I’m sure people abused it. But there was just absolutely no need for Karen’s condescending and rude attitude.</Review>

I've been with Orkin for more than 10 years and and can highly recommend them.  I should have written prior to this as I've never had any complaints and only the most positive of experiences.  Important to me is communication - and it is very easy to do so...  with  an actual human being! . I can contact my usual technician on his cell phone, or the office is always great too. Today, for example, was typical of their exemplary service.... first, setting the stage: IT'S A FRIDAY AFTERNOON DURING COVID PANDEMIC AND CALIFORNIA UNDER QUARANTINE - so when I came home to find a swarm of bees outside my daughters window - and she suffers from a moderate allergic reaction - I was in a bit of a panic. < Text>
I live within the city limits of San Diego. Just over the years ago, the city removed the leftovers of a building that they tore down 12 years ago (about time, right?). The problem was that mice and rats had moved into the piles of wood and other stuff. When they cleared out the piles, the mice and rats moved into the houses closest to the piles. I was a block away, but was over-run. In less than two months, I had over $22,000 in damage. They are the electrical wires, two sofas, all of the ducts for hearing and air. Orkin (I already had a monthly service contract) was at my house every day (sometimes multiple times a day) until the problem was solved. They did a great job and worked long hours. I continue with the monthly service, but if I see, hear or suspect that I might have a rat or mouse, they respond (usually within two hours) to help me out. I recommend their service and know that if you have a pest problem, they will work to correct the problem.< /Text>
